	(27, NULL, NULL, NULL, 7, 2, 0, NULL, '<p>You need to configure the devices in Beijing to use authentication methods other than standard passwords.<br><br>Which three authentication methods should you use? Each correct answer presents a complete solution.</p>', '<p id="explanationBodyText"><p>You should use picture passwords, PIN numbers, or fingerprint passwords (fingerprint recognition). Picture passwords and PIN numbers can be used on all Windows 10 devices, including laptops and tablets. Fingerprint authentication requires a fingerprint scanner attached to the Windows device, which the Beijing devices have.<br><br>You should not use Windows Hello with facial recognition. Facial recognition requires that your Windows device has a near-infrared camera.<br><br>You should not use voice recognition. Windows 10 supports speech recognition as an input option, but does not support voice as an authentication option.<br><br><strong>References<br><br></strong><a title="Windows 10 authentication options leave passwords behind" href="https://searchenterprisedesktop.techtarget.com/tip/Windows-10-authentication-options-leave-passwords-behind" target="_blank" rel="noopener" tabindex="190">Windows 10 authentication options leave passwords behind</a><br><br><a title="Windows Hello face authentication" href="https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/windows-hardware/design/device-experiences/windows-hello-face-authentication" target="_blank" rel="noopener" tabindex="190">Windows Hello face authentication</a><br><br><a title="Use speech recognition " href="https://support.microsoft.com/en-us/help/17208/windows-10-use-speech-recognition" target="_blank" rel="noopener" tabindex="190">Use speech recognition </a><br><br><a title="What is Windows Hello?" href="https://support.microsoft.com/en-us/help/17215/windows-10-what-is-hello" target="_blank" rel="noopener" tabindex="190">What is Windows Hello?</a><br><br><a title="Windows 10 Tutorials 44 - How to Setup Picture Password" href="https://www.