	(1, NULL, NULL, NULL, 2, 'scene.chapter', NULL, '<p>You are the administrator of Company1\'s devices. Your company acquires Company2, and you are tasked with configuring devices from Company2 to conform to Company1\'s policies.<br><br>Company1 corporate policies require the following:<br><br>* All devices must run Windows 10 Enterprise.<br>* All devices in the IT department must use Hyper-V and virtual smart cards.<br>* All devices in the Sales department must use Secure Boot.<br>* All devices in the Development department must use Hyper-V.<br><br>Existing Company2 devices are shown in the Company2 devices exhibit.<br><br>After the re-organization, you need to provide devices for the following departments:<br><br>* 75 for IT <br>* 25 for Sales <br>* 50 for Development<br><br>Current devices can be moved between departments as necessary to meet the requirements if it does not adversely affect other departments.<br><br>You have the following requirements:<br><br>* Minimize the number of new devices to purchase.<br>* Minimize the time required to upgrade the operating system.<br>* Existing applications should remain on the existing devices if possible.</p>', NULL, 'csMS_70-698-CS-001-cs1.jpeg', 1, NULL, 1),
	(2, NULL, NULL, NULL, 2, 'scene.chapter', 'Upgrade AD', NULL, '<p>This case study contains a series of questions that use the same or similar answer choices. An answer choice may be correct for more than one question in the series. Each question is independent of the other questions in this series. Information and details provided in a question apply only to that question.\n\n</p>', NULL, 1, NULL, 2),
	(3, NULL, NULL, NULL, 2, 'scene.chapter', NULL, NULL, '<p>This case study contains a series of questions that use the same or similar answer choices. An answer choice may be correct for more than one question in the series. Each question is independent of the other questions in this series. Information and details provided in a question apply only to that question.\n', NULL, 1, NULL, 3),
	(4, NULL, NULL, NULL, 2, 'scene.chapter', NULL, NULL, '<p>This case study contains a series of questions that use the same or similar answer choices. An answer choice may be correct for more than one question in the series. Each question is independent of the other questions in this series. Information and details provided in a question apply only to that question.\n', NULL, 1, NULL, 4),
	(5, NULL, NULL, NULL, 2, 'scene.chapter', 'Storage Solutions', NULL, '<p>This case study contains a series of questions that use the same or similar answer choices. An answer choice may be correct for more than one question in the series. Each question is independent of the other questions in this series. Information and details provided in a question apply only to that question.\n', NULL, 1, NULL, 5),
	(6, NULL, NULL, NULL, 2, 'scene.chapter', NULL, '<p>You are setting up a home automation network that consists of the following devices:<br><br>* One Network Attached Storage (NAS) device<br>* Four laptop computers upgraded from Windows 7 SP1 to Windows 10<br>* Four tablet devices upgraded from Windows 7 SP1 to Windows 10<br>* One Wireless printing device<br><br>You want to ensure that all users in your home have their information backed up at all time. All devices need to be able to be restored to an earlier point. All Office documents must retain older versions. All mobile devices should synchronize to the cloud when outside of the home, and to the NAS when inside it.</p>', '<p>This case study contains a series of questions that use the same or similar answer choices. An answer choice may be correct for more than one question in the series. Each question is independent of the other questions in this series. Information and details provided in a question apply only to that question.\n</p>', NULL, 1, NULL, 6),
	(7, NULL, NULL, NULL, 2, 'scene.chapter', NULL, '<p>You are the administrator for the CompanyA Windows environment. Management is concerned that users traveling with laptop computers could expose confidential information if the laptops are lost or stolen. Some of the risks include simple passwords, and users writing down passwords, which are then stored with the machines. \n\nYour environment consists of the devices shown in the Devices exhibit.\n\nYou must configure the machines to use alternative logon methods.\n</p>', '<p>This case study contains a series of questions that use the same or similar answer choices. An answer choice may be correct for more than one question in the series. Each question is independent of the other questions in this series. Information and details provided in a question apply only to that question.\n</p>', 'csMS_70-698-CS-008_table.jpeg', 1, NULL, 7),
